We are looking for another student intern. This person will primarily be
doing neutron detector development work. The main focus will be MCNP
calculations to model neutron detection and measurement to support
calculations.

The intern would be full time for the summer of 2002 (~May 15 - August 15).
The pay will vary between non-BS and grad student, but in ballpark of
$700/week gross. The following is the position description as posted
internally.

Candidate will serve as a Scientific Assistant in the Technical Operations
Section, primarily supporting Site Directed Research and Development
projects. Candidate will assist Principal Investigators in modeling;
computer programming; designing and testing equipment; acquiring and
analyzing radiation data; and generating reports.

Enrolled in BS or graduate program in Physics, Computer Science,
Physical/Nuclear Chemistry, Nuclear Engineering, Health Physics, or related
field. Familiarity with radiation detectors, associated electronics, and
data acquisition systems is desired. Computer programming skills are
desired.

Hope all is well,
Carson

